<paragraph id="8BA336D73A139C19E4C3FD03C9A85CB1" blockId="2.[151,1437,620,1053]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<keyLead id="30ED95E23A139C19E4C3FD03C9A85CB1" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
- Anterior half of pronotum with central tubercle usually distinctly shorter than width at base (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E01FFD03C8A45CFB" box="[1099,1168,679,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1368,258,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Brachycerocoris petrii sp. nov. a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (ventral), c, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531710/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E0CDFD03C8E85CFA" box="[1177,1244,679,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
) and apex of central tubercle distinctly rounded, if as long as width at base, the central tubercle at basal half of scutellum (scutellar tubercle) much elongate (&gt; 
<quantity id="4CE49B323A139C19E51AFD46CDB25CB0" box="[334,390,738,759]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in height) (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E5A2FD45CE085CB0" box="[502,572,737,759]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1123,1147]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,219,1068]" captionTargetId="figure-31@10.[151,1436,181,1099]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Habitus of Brachycerocoris davidii sp. nov. a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral); c, Habitus (ventral). Lettering: mt–mandibular plate tubercle. Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531714/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
)..................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A139C19E1C4FD45C9A85CB1" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,737,758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
