<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B57BE3A139C19E104FCB8C9A85D76" box="[1360,1436,796,817]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA336D73A139C19E4C3FC9EC9A85D08" blockId="2.[151,1437,620,1053]" box="[151,1436,825,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<keyLead id="30ED95E23A139C19E4C3FC9EC9A85D08" box="[151,1436,825,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A139C19E4C3FC9ECCAB5D08" bold="true" box="[151,159,826,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">-</emphasis>
Central tubercle at basal half of scutellum (scutellar tubercle) short with 
<quantity id="4CE49B323A139C19E7CEFC9ECFE55D08" box="[922,977,826,847]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
in height (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E06EFC9DC8B45D08" box="[1082,1152,825,847]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1368,258,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Brachycerocoris petrii sp. nov. a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (ventral), c, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531710/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E0DEFC9DC8FA5D08" box="[1162,1230,825,847]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
).............. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E82E723A139C19E4C3FCF3C9A85A5A" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<paragraph id="8BA336D73A139C19E4C3FCF3C9A85D83" blockId="2.[151,1437,620,1053]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<keyLead id="30ED95E23A139C19E4C3FCF3C9A85D83" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A139C19E4C3FCF3CC975D2B" bold="true" box="[151,163,855,876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">3</emphasis>
The central margin connecting base of central tubercle on basal half of scutellum with posteromedial scutellar tubercle, straight (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E5DFFCD0CDE75DCD" box="[395,467,884,906]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[191,1368,258,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus of Brachycerocoris petrii sp. nov. a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (ventral), c, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531710/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
); Paramere distinctly P-shaped, apex of crown broader than long, crown massive (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E0A1FCD0C9685DCD" box="[1269,1372,884,906]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1366,1390]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,190,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1342]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Brachycerocoris petrii sp. nov. (male genitalia–line drawings). a, genital capsule (dorsal); b, genital capsule (ventral); c, genital capsule (caudal); d &amp; e, paramere (different planes). Lettering: ca–caudal angles; dr–dorsal rim; vr–ventral rim. Scale bar equals 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531727/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 9 d, e</figureCitation>
); stem medially concave on outer margin and not of uniform width throughout................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D543A139C19E7DDFC0BC97C5D82" authority="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs" authorityName="Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs" authorityYear="2021" box="[905,1352,943,965]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspidae" genus="Brachycerocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A139C19E7DDFC0BC8565D83" box="[905,1122,943,964]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Brachycerocoris petrii</emphasis>
Salini &amp; Roca-Cusachs
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B57BE3A139C19E11AFC0BC9A85D83" box="[1358,1436,943,964]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B968EAC53A139C19E11AFC0BC9A25D83" bold="true" box="[1358,1430,943,964]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA336D73A139C19E4C3FC69C9A85A5A" blockId="2.[151,1437,620,1053]" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
<keyLead id="30ED95E23A139C19E4C3FC69C9A85A5A" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">
