<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E581FC4DCE295DB8" box="[469,541,1001,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1337,1361]" captionTargetBox="[169,1384,189,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1436,181,1313]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3.Habitus of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (Vollenhoven). a, Habitus (dorsal); b, Habitus (lateral). Scale bar equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531712" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531712/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); Paramere distinctly L-shaped, apex of crown semiovate, crown not massive (
<figureCitation id="13272A523A139C19E149FC4DC9A45DB8" box="[1309,1424,1001,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1012,1036]" captionTargetBox="[233,1362,199,977]" captionTargetId="figure-31@18.[215,1372,181,988]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 13. Details of Brachycerocoris dromedarius (male genitalia). a &amp; b paramere (different planes); c, phallus (dorsal); d, phallus (ventral); e, phallus (lateral); f, phallus (caudal); g, spermatheca; h, female terminalia. Lettering:ad–aedeagus; dcp–dorsolateral conjunctival processes; rs–ring sclerites; vcp–ventral conjunctival processes. Scale bar equals 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531736" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531736/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="509">Fig. 13 a, b</figureCitation>
); stem of uniform width throughout..................................... 
